cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper proposes a new memory scheduler design for multicore systems, which can be considered an architectural improvement. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems): The paper addresses the problem of inter-application interference in multicore systems, which is a common issue in operating systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new system-level solution to improve performance and fairness in multicore systems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on improving performance and fairness in multicore systems, which can be considered a form of parallel computing. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper proposes a new memory scheduler design to improve system performance and fairness, which falls under the category of performance optimization.
